00090 static void outliner_storage_cleanup(SpaceOops *soops)
00091 {
00092     TreeStore *ts= soops->treestore;
00093     
00094     if (ts) {
00095         TreeStoreElem *tselem;
00096         int a, unused= 0;
00097         
00098         /* each element used once, for ID blocks with more users to have each a treestore */
00099         for (a=0, tselem= ts->data; a<ts->usedelem; a++, tselem++) tselem->used= 0;
00100         
00101         /* cleanup only after reading file or undo step, and always for
00102          * RNA datablocks view in order to save memory */
00103         if (soops->storeflag & SO_TREESTORE_CLEANUP) {
00104             
00105             for (a=0, tselem= ts->data; a<ts->usedelem; a++, tselem++) {
00106                 if (tselem->id==NULL) unused++;
00107             }
00108             
00109             if (unused) {
00110                 if (ts->usedelem == unused) {
00111                     MEM_freeN(ts->data);
00112                     ts->data= NULL;
00113                     ts->usedelem= ts->totelem= 0;
00114                 }
00115                 else {
00116                     TreeStoreElem *tsnewar, *tsnew;
00117                     
00118                     tsnew=tsnewar= MEM_mallocN((ts->usedelem-unused)*sizeof(TreeStoreElem), "new tselem");
00119                     for (a=0, tselem= ts->data; a<ts->usedelem; a++, tselem++) {
00120                         if (tselem->id) {
00121                             *tsnew= *tselem;
00122                             tsnew++;
00123                         }
00124                     }
00125                     MEM_freeN(ts->data);
00126                     ts->data= tsnewar;
00127                     ts->usedelem-= unused;
00128                     ts->totelem= ts->usedelem;
00129                 }
00130             }
00131         }
00132     }
00133 }

00135 static void check_persistent(SpaceOops *soops, TreeElement *te, ID *id, short type, short nr)
00136 {
00137     TreeStore *ts;
00138     TreeStoreElem *tselem;
00139     int a;
00140     
00141     /* case 1; no TreeStore */
00142     if (soops->treestore==NULL) {
00143         soops->treestore= MEM_callocN(sizeof(TreeStore), "treestore");
00144     }
00145     ts= soops->treestore;
00146     
00147     /* check if 'te' is in treestore */
00148     tselem= ts->data;
00149     for (a=0; a<ts->usedelem; a++, tselem++) {
00150         if (tselem->id==id && tselem->used==0) {
00151             if ((type==0 && tselem->type==0) ||(tselem->type==type && tselem->nr==nr)) {
00152                 te->store_index= a;
00153                 tselem->used= 1;
00154                 return;
00155             }
00156         }
00157     }
00158     
00159     /* add 1 element to treestore */
00160     if (ts->usedelem==ts->totelem) {
00161         TreeStoreElem *tsnew;
00162         
00163         tsnew= MEM_mallocN((ts->totelem+TS_CHUNK)*sizeof(TreeStoreElem), "treestore data");
00164         if (ts->data) {
00165             memcpy(tsnew, ts->data, ts->totelem*sizeof(TreeStoreElem));
00166             MEM_freeN(ts->data);
00167         }
00168         ts->data= tsnew;
00169         ts->totelem+= TS_CHUNK;
00170     }
00171     
00172     tselem= ts->data+ts->usedelem;
00173     
00174     tselem->type= type;
00175     if (type) tselem->nr= nr; // we're picky! :)
00176     else tselem->nr= 0;
00177     tselem->id= id;
00178     tselem->used = 0;
00179     tselem->flag= TSE_CLOSED;
00180     te->store_index= ts->usedelem;
00181     
00182     ts->usedelem++;
00183 }

00208 static TreeElement *outliner_find_tree_element(ListBase *lb, int store_index)
00209 {
00210     TreeElement *te= lb->first, *tes;
00211     while (te) {
00212         if (te->store_index==store_index) return te;
00213         tes= outliner_find_tree_element(&te->subtree, store_index);
00214         if (tes) return tes;
00215         te= te->next;
00216     }
00217     return NULL;

00220 /* tse is not in the treestore, we use its contents to find a match */
00221 TreeElement *outliner_find_tse(SpaceOops *soops, TreeStoreElem *tse)
00222 {
00223     TreeStore *ts= soops->treestore;
00224     TreeStoreElem *tselem;

00226     
00227     if (tse->id==NULL) return NULL;

00229     /* check if 'tse' is in treestore */
00230     tselem= ts->data;
00231     for (a=0; a<ts->usedelem; a++, tselem++) {
00232         if ((tse->type==0 && tselem->type==0) || (tselem->type==tse->type && tselem->nr==tse->nr)) {
00233             if (tselem->id==tse->id) {
00234                 break;
00235             }
00236         }
00237     }
00238     if (tselem) 
00239         return outliner_find_tree_element(&soops->tree, a);
00240     
00241     return NULL;

00244 /* Find treestore that refers to given ID */
00245 TreeElement *outliner_find_id(SpaceOops *soops, ListBase *lb, ID *id)
00246 {
00247     TreeElement *te, *tes;
00248     TreeStoreElem *tselem;
00249     
00250     for (te= lb->first; te; te= te->next) {
00251         tselem= TREESTORE(te);
00252         if (tselem->type==0) {
00253             if (tselem->id==id) return te;
00254             /* only deeper on scene or object */
00255             if ( te->idcode==ID_OB || te->idcode==ID_SCE || (soops->outlinevis == SO_GROUPS && te->idcode==ID_GR)) {
00256                 tes= outliner_find_id(soops, &te->subtree, id);
00257                 if (tes) return tes;
00258             }
00259         }
00260     }
00261     return NULL;
00262 }

00551             }

00553                 outliner_add_element(soops, &te->subtree, ((ArmatureModifierData*) md)->object, te, TSE_LINKED_OB, 0);

00557             }

00559                 TreeElement *ten;
00560                 ParticleSystem *psys= ((ParticleSystemModifierData*) md)->psys;
00561                 
00562                 ten = outliner_add_element(soops, &te->subtree, ob, te, TSE_LINKED_PSYS, 0);
00563                 ten->directdata = psys;
00564                 ten->name = psys->part->id.name+2;
00565             }
00566         }
00567     }
00568     
00569     /* vertex groups */
00570     if (ob->defbase.first) {
00571         bDeformGroup *defgroup;
00572         TreeElement *ten;
00573         TreeElement *tenla= outliner_add_element(soops, &te->subtree, ob, te, TSE_DEFGROUP_BASE, 0);
00574         
00575         tenla->name= "Vertex Groups";
00576         for (defgroup=ob->defbase.first, a=0; defgroup; defgroup=defgroup->next, a++) {

00578             ten->name= defgroup->name;

00582

00584     if (ob->dup_group)
00585         outliner_add_element(soops, &te->subtree, ob->dup_group, te, 0, 0); 
00586 }

01090 /* Helped function to put duplicate sequence in the same tree. */
01091 static int need_add_seq_dup(Sequence *seq)
01092 {
01093     Sequence *p;
01094 
01095     if ((!seq->strip) || (!seq->strip->stripdata) || (!seq->strip->stripdata->name))
01096         return(1);
01097 
01098     /*
01099      * First check backward, if we found a duplicate
01100      * sequence before this, don't need it, just return.
01101      */
01102     p= seq->prev;
01103     while (p) {
01104         if ((!p->strip) || (!p->strip->stripdata) || (!p->strip->stripdata->name)) {
01105             p= p->prev;
01106             continue;
01107         }
01108 
01109         if (!strcmp(p->strip->stripdata->name, seq->strip->stripdata->name))
01110             return(2);
01111         p= p->prev;
01112     }
01113 
01114     p= seq->next;
01115     while (p) {
01116         if ((!p->strip) || (!p->strip->stripdata) || (!p->strip->stripdata->name)) {
01117             p= p->next;
01118             continue;
01119         }
01120 
01121         if (!strcmp(p->strip->stripdata->name, seq->strip->stripdata->name))
01122             return(0);
01123         p= p->next;
01124     }
01125     return(1);
01126 }

01130     /* TreeElement *ch; */ /* UNUSED */

01187 /* alphabetical comparator */
01188 static int treesort_alpha(const void *v1, const void *v2)
01189 {
01190     const tTreeSort *x1= v1, *x2= v2;
01191     int comp;
01192     
01193     /* first put objects last (hierarchy) */
01194     comp= (x1->idcode==ID_OB);
01195     if (x2->idcode==ID_OB) comp+=2;
01196     
01197     if (comp==1) return 1;
01198     else if (comp==2) return -1;
01199     else if (comp==3) {
01200         comp= strcmp(x1->name, x2->name);
01201         
01202         if ( comp>0 ) return 1;
01203         else if ( comp<0) return -1;
01204         return 0;
01205     }
01206     return 0;
01207 }

01236 /* sort happens on each subtree individual */
01237 static void outliner_sort(SpaceOops *soops, ListBase *lb)
01238 {
01239     TreeElement *te;
01240     TreeStoreElem *tselem;
01241     int totelem=0;
01242     
01243     te= lb->last;
01244     if (te==NULL) return;
01245     tselem= TREESTORE(te);
01246     
01247     /* sorting rules; only object lists or deformgroups */
01248     if ( (tselem->type==TSE_DEFGROUP) || (tselem->type==0 && te->idcode==ID_OB)) {
01249         
01250         /* count first */
01251         for (te= lb->first; te; te= te->next) totelem++;
01252         
01253         if (totelem>1) {
01254             tTreeSort *tear= MEM_mallocN(totelem*sizeof(tTreeSort), "tree sort array");
01255             tTreeSort *tp=tear;

01258             for (te= lb->first; te; te= te->next, tp++) {
01259                 tselem= TREESTORE(te);
01260                 tp->te= te;

01262                 tp->idcode= te->idcode;
01263                 if (tselem->type && tselem->type!=TSE_DEFGROUP) tp->idcode= 0;  // don't sort this
01264                 tp->id= tselem->id;
01265             }
01266             /* keep beginning of list */
01267             for (tp= tear, skip=0; skip<totelem; skip++, tp++)
01268                 if (tp->idcode) break;
01269             
01270             if (skip<totelem)
01271                 qsort(tear+skip, totelem-skip, sizeof(tTreeSort), treesort_alpha);
01272             
01273             lb->first=lb->last= NULL;
01274             tp= tear;
01275             while (totelem--) {
01276                 BLI_addtail(lb, tp->te);
01277                 tp++;
01278             }
01279             MEM_freeN(tear);
01280         }
01281     }
01282     
01283     for (te= lb->first; te; te= te->next) {
01284         outliner_sort(soops, &te->subtree);

01328 static int outliner_filter_tree(SpaceOops *soops, ListBase *lb)
01329 {
01330     TreeElement *te, *ten;
01331     TreeStoreElem *tselem;
01332     
01333     /* although we don't have any search string, we return TRUE 
01334      * since the entire tree is ok then...
01335      */
01336     if (soops->search_string[0]==0) 
01337         return 1;
01338 
01339     for (te= lb->first; te; te= ten) {
01340         ten= te->next;
01341         
01342         if (0==outliner_filter_has_name(te, soops->search_string, soops->search_flags)) {
01343             /* item isn't something we're looking for, but...
01344              *  - if the subtree is expanded, check if there are any matches that can be easily found
01345              *      so that searching for "cu" in the default scene will still match the Cube
01346              *  - otherwise, we can't see within the subtree and the item doesn't match,
01347              *      so these can be safely ignored (i.e. the subtree can get freed)
01348              */
01349             tselem= TREESTORE(te);
01350             
01351             /* flag as not a found item */
01352             tselem->flag &= ~TSE_SEARCHMATCH;
01353             
01354             if ((!TSELEM_OPEN(tselem,soops)) || outliner_filter_tree(soops, &te->subtree)==0) { 
01355                 outliner_free_tree(&te->subtree);
01356                 BLI_remlink(lb, te);
01357                 
01358                 if (te->flag & TE_FREE_NAME) MEM_freeN((void *)te->name);
01359                 MEM_freeN(te);
01360             }
01361         }
01362         else {
01363             tselem= TREESTORE(te);
01364             
01365             /* flag as a found item - we can then highlight it */
01366             tselem->flag |= TSE_SEARCHMATCH;
01367             
01368             /* filter subtree too */
01369             outliner_filter_tree(soops, &te->subtree);
01370         }
01371     }
01372     
01373     /* if there are still items in the list, that means that there were still some matches */
01374     return (lb->first != NULL);
